  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency health care to conflict-affected population in transit centres in Chad</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WHO and UNICEF are jointly responding in the two new transit centers at Danamadia and Maingama in Southern Chad.  Primary health services and curative consultations will be provided on site,  community health services will allow for early detection of malaria, diarrheaa, pneumonia, measles and other health issues and secondary health care will be provided by district health hospitals facilitated by WHO through the hiring of paramedics.  Emergency health and diarrhoea kits will be provided to the district hospital.  This joint 3 month response will support at least 40,000 of the conflict affected populations in the transit centres.</narrative>
  </description>
